s\n\n- Bluenscottish\n|\nWhen we can see the star of desire in our sky, we can use our wings of hope and our air of love to reach it.\n\n- Imania\n|\nUnless someone has lived your life, no one can live your dream!\n\n- Stephen\n|\nThe point of dreams was never to be the affordable option, it was the one everyone else saw as a mistake and every creative person saw as an opportunity.\n\n- Anastasia\n|\nThe job of the writer is to take a close and uncomfortable look at the world they inhabit, the world we all inhabit, and the job of the novel is to make the corpse stink.\n\n- Walter\n|\nThe living WORD, medicine for the soul.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nBeing creative, joyful, happy, and beloved are the ultimate purposes of a profound life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nDiscovering how the Universe will manifest all of your dreams for you is going to be an exciting journey that will harmonize the trinity of your mind, body and spirit.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Ask and the Universe Will Provide: A Straightforward Guide to Manifesting Your Dreams\n|\nSpiritual leaders, priests and prophets are lamps burning in the dark, seeking meaning for humanity.\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, Pearls Of Eternity\n|\nIf life is a song, you must be the superb lyrics to a sweet melody.\n\n- Amaka Imani Nkosazana, Release The Ink\n|\nGod Almighty, I don’t want to ask for more. But to say more thanks.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nI would like to invite everyone for the Third World War, but fight the war with love, not with the gun, to win the world peace. We all will be a winner.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nEvery time a war ends, under a beautiful sun, on the face of a crying child; I see a rainbow of hope over the innocent teardrops.\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nIf you don't keep challenging your mind and your self, you're going to loose the ability to grow as a human being both physically and spiritually.\n\n- Lateef\n|\nThe vastness of your imagination depends on the level of your consciousness, the power of your awareness, and the deepness of your perception.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nAll positive interactions with other human beings involve, to some degree, the experience of visibility-- that is, the experience of being seen and understood.\n\n- Nathaniel\n|\nThis is a long goodbye, yet not time enough. I have no aptitude for this. I cannot learn this. I would hold on, and hold on, until my hands clutch at emptiness.\n\n- Juliet Marillier, Son of the Shadows\n|\nEach time I see a beautiful sunset or sunrise, I have to pinch myself because I can't believe that I'm awake and not dreaming.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nThe peculiarity of sunrise is to make us laugh at all our terrors of the night, and our laugh is always proportioned to the fear we have had.\n\n- Victor Hugo, Les Misérables\n|\nSo that others can live in peace, talk about love and peace wherever you go.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf you're male, and you're Christian and living in America, your father is your model for God. And sometimes you find your father in your career.\n\n- Chuck Palahniuk, Fight Club\n|\nAlways direct your emotions, desires, behaviour, and actions in the present so they are in alignment with what you want in your future.\n\n- Mensah Oteh, Unlocking Life's Treasure Chest: Wisdom keys to keep you inspired, encouraged, motivated and focused\n|\nDon't you oh well me,sir,' Miss Maudie replied, recognizing Jem's fatalistic noises, 'you are not old enough to appreciate what I said.\n\n- Harper\n|\nI had come down here, not to serve God as a craftsman should, but to show my people how great a craftsman I was. They cared not.\n\n- Rudyard Kipling, Puck of Pook's Hill\n|\nYou are born to be wild but end up being named, tamed and chained.\n\n- Haresh\n|\nI would much rather be considered wise than smart. But, I still think it is wise to get an education.\n\n- Destiny\n|\nThe ego lusts for satisfaction. It has a prideful ferocious appetite for its version of 'truth'. It is the most challenging aspect to conquer; the cause for most spiritual turmoil.\n\n- T.F. Hodge, From Within I Rise: Spiritual Triumph Over Death and Conscious Encounters with 'The Divine Presence'\n|\nI have been here before, But when or how I cannot tell: I know the grass beyond the door, The sweet keen smell, The sighing sound, the lights around the shore.\n\n- Dante Gabriel Rossetti, The Complete Poetical Works of Dante Gabriel Rossetti\n|\nFrom whichever side I start, I think I am in an old place where others have been before me.\n\n- Dejan Stojanovic, The Sun Watches the Sun\n|\nBut yield who will to their separation, My object in living is to uniteMy avocation and my vocationAs my two eyes make one in sight.\n\n- Robert\n|\nEvery true love and friendship is a story of unexpected transformation. If we are the same person before and after we loved, that means we haven't loved enough.\n\n- Elif Shafak, The Forty Rules of Love\n|\nLife is not a Race, but we still continue the Chase and try to be an Ace. It’s time to get out of this Maze and Truly Live with Grace.\n\n- RVM\n|\nDive again and again into the river of uncertainty. Create in the dark, only then can you recognize the light.\n\n- Jyrki\n|\nIn the name of being social, we learn to ignore our natural instinct.Society keeps dictating do's and don'ts which we keep obeying day in and day out.\n\n- Chitralekha Paul, Delayed Monsoon\n|\nYou are one thought away from intelligence, one word away from kindness, one deed away from excellence, one step away from brilliance, and one second away from transcendence.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nBe a team player, not a bandwagon jumper.\n\n- Aaron Lauritsen, 100 Days Drive: The Great North American Road Trip\n|\nwe talk of plans that are going to happen.we talk of the future,as if we know we will last.there is a sort of comfort in that.\n\n- Ava, This Is How You Know I Want You.\n|\nTaking care of yourself doesn't mean me first, it means me too.\n\n- L.R.\n|\nHappiness is not a matter of intensity but of balance, order, rhythm and harmony.\n\n- Orison\n|\nThe streets of America may not have been paved with gold, but they were cobbled in middle-class dreams.\n\n- Regina Lee Blaszczyk, American Consumer Society, 1865-2005: From Hearth to HDTV (The American History) (American History Series)\n|\nNobody can steal my inner beauty, tranquility, and peace without my consent.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIt seems an insult to the night to speak of purpose and intent, when this common moment is so brimming full of blessed design tranquility. All things follow their course.\n\n- Anne Rice, The Claiming of Sleeping Beauty\n|\nDon't live in the dreams, don't fly high, don't keep the expectations that cause your death before the death.\n\n- Ehsan\n|\nMind with full of creative ideas and new thoughts, doesn't care what other will say or think.\n\n- Dipti\n|\nRun your own race of life, with a single minded vision of purpose.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nDeath is nature’s way of saying, ‘Your table is ready.\n\n- Robin\n|\nYOU'RE ONLY PUTTING OFF THE INEVITABLE, he said.That's what being alive is all about.\n\n- Terry Pratchett, Sourcery\n|\nAnd then in a moment of pure magic, our lips touch tenderly and sensitively!\n\n- Avijeet\n|\nGrief is like the ocean; it comes on waves ebbing and flowing. Sometimes the water is calm, and sometimes it is overwhelming. All we can do is learn to swim.\n\n- Vicki\n|\nA small crack in a wall, the wall might fall. A small crack in a relationship, several walls get created.\n\n- Santosh Avvannavar, He Who Dreams\n|\nBecause at nightwhen others are sleeping, I drown myself in poetry.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nOnce you die, that’s it – game over.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Principia Humanitas\n|\nHe inherited some good instincts from his Quaker forebearers, but by diligent hard work, he overcame them.\n\n- James\n|\nYou can only die once, to make sure it's worth it.\n\n- Vladimir\n|\nThe loudest preacher in the world is your conscience